WEBVTT

00:07.340 --> 00:09.300
[dramatic music]

00:09.384 --> 00:17.183
♪ ♪

00:25.692 --> 00:27.318
- You found me again.

00:27.402 --> 00:32.323
♪ ♪

00:32.407 --> 00:33.283
- You're dying.

00:33.366 --> 00:38.997
♪ ♪

00:41.958 --> 00:43.835
He shot you with poison.

00:43.918 --> 00:46.129
He used to be a dentist.

00:46.212 --> 00:50.300
♪ ♪

00:50.383 --> 00:53.595
- [spits]

00:53.678 --> 00:55.430
- This is the antidote.

00:55.513 --> 00:57.140
- Give it.

00:57.223 --> 01:03.354
♪ ♪

01:04.731 --> 01:06.941
Wait.

01:07.025 --> 01:13.031
♪ ♪

01:28.671 --> 01:32.217
[breathing heavily]

01:40.767 --> 01:42.977
[inhales deeply]

01:47.524 --> 01:50.401
[eerie creaking and whooshing]

02:01.204 --> 02:03.373
- Hey, Jeev.

02:03.456 --> 02:04.123
- Yeah?

02:08.545 --> 02:12.131
- You still scared of the dark?

02:12.215 --> 02:13.216
- Yeah.

02:17.720 --> 02:21.516
[metal groaning]

02:42.579 --> 02:45.623
[wind whistling]

02:47.542 --> 02:50.587
- It's like a spaceship.
- We're fucked.

02:51.170 --> 02:55.133
[tense piano music]

02:55.216 --> 02:56.801
- It's gonna get cold.

02:59.512 --> 03:01.472
[tender music]

03:01.556 --> 03:08.438
♪ ♪

03:08.521 --> 03:10.940
- Jeevan.

03:14.319 --> 03:14.819
- It's gonna be okay.

03:14.903 --> 03:17.113
- You said we're fucked.

03:20.199 --> 03:23.202
- When spring comes,
we're gonna run out of food.

03:25.371 --> 03:27.790
Whoever's left alive is gonna
want to fight each other.

03:29.709 --> 03:31.419
We have to think
about the future.

03:31.502 --> 03:36.090
We have to leave,
because this...

03:36.174 --> 03:37.800
can't last.

03:37.884 --> 03:43.806
♪ ♪

03:43.890 --> 03:46.809
[clock ticking]

03:46.893 --> 03:49.145
[tense music]

03:50.855 --> 03:52.357
- I spy with my little eye.

03:52.440 --> 03:53.816
- I told Jeevan
to come to you.

03:53.900 --> 03:55.818
You guys should be together.

03:55.902 --> 03:59.364
- No. No, no. No.

03:59.447 --> 04:00.323
No, I don't want him here.

04:00.406 --> 04:02.742
- I don't care
if you don't want Jeevan--

04:02.825 --> 04:04.577
♪ ♪

04:04.661 --> 04:06.579
- Then I'll have
the guard stop him.

04:10.792 --> 04:11.668
[sighs]

04:11.751 --> 04:14.712
[phone ringing]

04:14.796 --> 04:21.844
♪ ♪

04:42.031 --> 04:44.575
- Good evening, Mr. Chaudhary.
I've got a Jeevan down here.

04:44.659 --> 04:46.577
Says he's your brother.
He's with your niece.

04:46.661 --> 04:47.870
Want to come up.

04:47.954 --> 04:49.622
They've got some items
for your Christmas party.

04:49.706 --> 04:52.667
- Hey, Frank.
- Hi, Uncle Frank.

04:52.750 --> 04:54.585
- Send 'em up.

04:54.669 --> 04:55.920
Fuck!

04:56.004 --> 04:58.965
[jazzy music]

04:59.048 --> 05:05.638
♪ ♪

05:10.643 --> 05:12.520
[pounding on door]
- Frank! Open the door, Frank!

05:12.603 --> 05:14.355
- Hold on.
- Come on!

05:14.439 --> 05:16.024
- Hold on!
- Open it!

05:18.276 --> 05:21.904
- Jeev.
Little white girl.

05:21.988 --> 05:24.574
- Okay, this is all comin' in.
Back up.

05:24.657 --> 05:26.617
Frank, this is Kirsten.
Kirsten, Frank.

05:26.701 --> 05:28.703
- Hi.
- We seem to be experiencing

05:28.786 --> 05:30.621
some technical difficulties
at the moment.

05:30.705 --> 05:33.082
- Hello, it's Matthew here.
Actually--

05:33.166 --> 05:36.753
- Paris is just fuckin'
on fire now.

05:36.836 --> 05:38.337
And there was a coup in China.

05:41.507 --> 05:42.925
Attempted.
- Reports of in excess

05:43.009 --> 05:44.469
of 10,000 deaths
coming in tonight.

05:44.552 --> 05:47.055
- Yeah, maybe you should
turn it off.

05:47.138 --> 05:48.473
- There hasn't been any news
on the Ferris wheel.

05:51.142 --> 05:52.602
- The story, here, Tina...
[line rings]

05:52.685 --> 05:53.936
Is the speed
at which this virus kills.

05:54.020 --> 05:55.772
- Imagine dying like that.

05:55.855 --> 05:58.191
- Well, the way I see it,

05:58.274 --> 05:59.609
power is on.

05:59.692 --> 06:00.943
Everything will be
back to normal

06:01.027 --> 06:02.653
in a couple of days.

06:05.198 --> 06:08.034
- Matthew, this news is
a somewhat radical escalation

06:08.117 --> 06:10.870
of what we've been hearing.

06:12.830 --> 06:15.541
- Uh, yes, that's correct,
Tina, yes.

06:15.625 --> 06:19.170
- What?

06:19.253 --> 06:21.339
- [speaking Hindi]

06:25.051 --> 06:28.805
- [speaking Hindi]

06:32.558 --> 06:35.394
[soft piano music]

06:46.072 --> 06:51.244
♪ ♪

06:51.327 --> 06:53.496
- Kirsten,

06:53.579 --> 06:58.292
maybe, uh--
do you want to get some sleep?

06:58.376 --> 07:00.169
There's a spare bedroom.

07:00.253 --> 07:06.050
♪ ♪

07:06.134 --> 07:08.427
- I'll tell you
when my parents call.

07:08.511 --> 07:09.720
Good night, Jeevan.
Good night, Frank.

07:09.804 --> 07:17.603
♪ ♪

07:20.314 --> 07:22.692
- Well, parenting is easy.

07:22.775 --> 07:30.533
♪ ♪

07:32.160 --> 07:35.997
[distant sirens wailing]

07:41.961 --> 07:44.463
[exhales heavily]

07:44.547 --> 07:48.092
[dramatic music]

07:48.176 --> 07:49.927
What's gonna happen?

07:50.720 --> 07:53.014
Really?

07:57.143 --> 07:58.561
- I don't know.

08:00.938 --> 08:02.481
But I'm glad you're here.

08:06.944 --> 08:08.654
How was "King Lear"?

08:13.242 --> 08:14.452
- [sighs]

08:14.535 --> 08:16.621
[clock ticking]

08:19.332 --> 08:20.458
- Frank?

08:24.003 --> 08:26.380
Merry Christmas.

08:28.841 --> 08:30.760
- That's right.

08:30.843 --> 08:33.262
I--I forgot.

08:33.346 --> 08:36.307
I didn't get you anything yet.

08:37.683 --> 08:40.102
- That's okay.

08:40.186 --> 08:41.020
Can I have that back?

08:41.103 --> 08:43.773
"Station Eleven"?

08:43.856 --> 08:45.900
- Sure.

08:47.610 --> 08:49.153
Just keep reading it.

08:49.237 --> 08:51.989
Should be doing my work.

08:52.073 --> 08:54.617
It's good, though.

08:54.700 --> 08:56.410
I can relate.

08:56.494 --> 08:57.662
- To which character?

09:00.873 --> 09:03.251
- All of them.

09:18.975 --> 09:20.309
- Did you put the antidote
in the present?

09:20.393 --> 09:23.437
I have to get back.
Where is it?

09:23.521 --> 09:26.315
Where is it?

09:26.399 --> 09:27.567
- I just made him something.

09:32.863 --> 09:34.865
You can go if you want to go.

09:37.243 --> 09:39.495
I hid the antidote
in your pocket.

09:39.578 --> 09:42.498
[delicate music]

09:42.581 --> 09:45.001
♪ ♪

09:45.084 --> 09:45.960
I knew you wouldn't look there.

09:46.043 --> 09:53.801
♪ ♪

10:12.653 --> 10:13.571
- No, I could stay a little.

10:22.288 --> 10:24.999
There's time.

10:25.082 --> 10:27.793
[festive music playing]

10:27.877 --> 10:34.925
♪ ♪

10:39.972 --> 10:41.724
- She's moving into the closet.

10:41.807 --> 10:43.976
- ♪ We wish you
a merry Christmas ♪

10:44.060 --> 10:47.021
Why do all kids love little
Harry Potter rooms like that?

10:47.104 --> 10:48.230
- ♪ We wish you
a merry Christmas ♪

10:48.314 --> 10:50.358
- To make the world small.

10:50.441 --> 10:53.736
- ♪ And a happy New Year ♪

10:53.819 --> 10:55.988
- You think she's okay?

10:56.072 --> 10:57.782
- She just found out
her parents died.

10:57.865 --> 11:01.869
She's eight. She's traumatized.

11:01.952 --> 11:03.120
- Makes three of us.

11:03.204 --> 11:06.290
- ♪ And a happy New Year ♪

11:06.374 --> 11:07.124
♪ Good tidings we bring ♪

11:07.208 --> 11:11.379
- Oh, come on, now.

11:11.462 --> 11:12.797
What's wrong with this--
what's wrong with this thing?

11:12.880 --> 11:16.509
- Seriously, how have you
made it this far in life?

11:16.592 --> 11:18.594
- [sighs]

11:18.677 --> 11:21.222
You got batteries?

11:21.305 --> 11:22.807
- Junk drawer.

11:22.890 --> 11:25.059
- ♪ We wish you
a crazy Christmas ♪

11:25.142 --> 11:28.396
♪ We wish you
a naughty Christmas ♪

11:28.479 --> 11:30.940
♪ And a frantic New Year ♪

11:31.023 --> 11:38.072
♪ ♪

11:45.246 --> 11:47.998
- Frank, can I talk to you
real quick in private?

11:48.082 --> 11:50.292
Uh, make us more eggnogs.
- Is there a recipe?

11:50.376 --> 11:53.254
- Pour whiskey into eggnog.

11:53.337 --> 11:59.718
♪ ♪

12:06.600 --> 12:09.186
What the fuck, Frank?
- It's not--

12:09.270 --> 12:11.230
- I'm sorry, heroin?
We're not heroin people, Frank.

12:11.313 --> 12:13.023
We're barely weed people.

12:13.107 --> 12:14.608
You win awards.

12:14.692 --> 12:15.985
- I quit. I'm clean. It's fine.

12:16.068 --> 12:16.527
- People don't just
quit heroin, Frank.

12:16.610 --> 12:18.571
Aren't you in withdrawal?

12:18.654 --> 12:20.906
- I don't have a cold.

12:22.533 --> 12:24.743
- When did you even start?
- Ten months ago.

12:28.914 --> 12:30.750
It's not sad, Jeevan.
It just--it just is.

12:30.833 --> 12:31.750
- It's not great, Frank!

12:37.590 --> 12:40.801
- I can't ghostwrite sober.

12:40.885 --> 12:42.470
- Then stop ghostwriting.

12:42.553 --> 12:43.846
- It's the only job I can get.

12:43.929 --> 12:45.931
- Frank, there are
no more jobs.

12:46.015 --> 12:46.849
- Okay.

12:46.932 --> 12:50.686
Whatever's going on
outside is irrelevant

12:50.769 --> 12:52.855
'cause I haven't been out
on assignment in two years.

12:53.522 --> 12:57.943
Whatever I had, it's gone.

12:58.027 --> 12:58.694
- It'll come back.

12:58.777 --> 13:01.739
- Journalists have
to go outside.

13:01.822 --> 13:04.366
- Then write a novel.
- I don't make shit up!

13:04.450 --> 13:07.411
[tense string music]

13:07.495 --> 13:14.543
♪ ♪

13:15.961 --> 13:17.379
- If we have to leave,
we leave together.

13:17.463 --> 13:19.882
You'll get better.
Your hip--

13:19.965 --> 13:23.719
- It's not the hip, Jeevan.

13:23.802 --> 13:29.808
♪ ♪

13:33.312 --> 13:35.439
- We have a kid now.

13:35.523 --> 13:42.571
♪ ♪

14:02.174 --> 14:04.051
- Listen to me.

14:04.134 --> 14:06.095
Don't write the play.

14:06.178 --> 14:08.180
- Hey, Kirsten.

14:08.264 --> 14:10.933
- You leave one day too late.

14:11.016 --> 14:17.565
♪ ♪

14:19.942 --> 14:22.987
- Will likely happen
in phases, I think.

14:23.070 --> 14:27.449
Networks and television have
already stopped broadcasting.

14:27.533 --> 14:31.620
Likely the phone system next,
and already, it's failing.

14:32.871 --> 14:34.790
Power and the Internet
will both hold on,

14:34.873 --> 14:37.626
and people who are holed up
will continue

14:37.710 --> 14:39.336
to find one another online,

14:39.420 --> 14:42.464
but this will only conceal
the reality

14:42.548 --> 14:46.010
that it's already over.

14:46.093 --> 14:49.471
We've encountered a flu
that does not incubate.

14:49.555 --> 14:52.016
It just explodes.

14:52.099 --> 14:58.063
We were not ready for
a 1-in-1,000 survival rate.

14:58.147 --> 15:01.734
Chicago's not Chicago anymore.

15:01.817 --> 15:05.070
It's just 2.5 million bodies
and--

15:28.552 --> 15:32.973
- ♪ The first Noel ♪

15:33.057 --> 15:36.727
♪ The angels did say ♪

15:36.810 --> 15:41.899
♪ Was to certain
poor shepherds ♪

15:41.982 --> 15:46.654
♪ In fields as they lay ♪

15:46.737 --> 15:50.616
♪ In fields where they ♪

15:50.699 --> 15:56.163
♪ Lay keeping their sheep ♪

15:56.246 --> 15:59.541
♪ On a cold winter's night ♪

15:59.625 --> 16:04.963
♪ That was so deep ♪

16:05.047 --> 16:10.052
♪ Noel, Noel ♪

16:10.135 --> 16:15.349
♪ Noel, Noel ♪

16:15.432 --> 16:18.936
♪ Born is the King ♪

16:19.019 --> 16:23.565
♪ of Israel ♪

16:29.321 --> 16:31.657
- Thanks.

16:34.493 --> 16:36.745
[sniffles]

16:36.829 --> 16:38.747
[clock ticking]

16:38.831 --> 16:39.915
- Any word from your parents?

16:44.128 --> 16:45.629
Frank.

16:45.713 --> 16:47.256
Jeevan's brother.

16:47.339 --> 16:49.758
Remember?

16:55.347 --> 16:58.142
You know,
first morning I was here,

16:58.225 --> 17:03.522
I remember the sun
rising over that lake, and...

17:03.605 --> 17:06.817
I knew I wanted
to be here forever.

17:11.864 --> 17:13.991
East-facing windows, you know?

17:17.202 --> 17:18.871
- Did you just move in?

17:20.164 --> 17:21.457
- Ten months ago.

17:21.540 --> 17:23.500
- What's your job?

17:23.584 --> 17:26.712
- I'm a ghostwriter.

17:26.795 --> 17:28.505
- What are you ghostwriting?

17:28.589 --> 17:32.384
- An autobiography.

17:32.468 --> 17:35.637
- Don't you have to write
your own autobiography?

17:35.721 --> 17:37.556
- Not if you're rich.

17:45.105 --> 17:49.777
[sighs]
Um...

17:49.860 --> 17:53.697
listen, Kirsten,
my brother does...

17:53.781 --> 17:56.241
weird shit sometimes.

17:57.576 --> 18:02.247
He--he brought home a bird once
that he found on the sidewalk

18:02.331 --> 18:04.500
with a broken neck.

18:04.583 --> 18:06.627
He's a terrible babysitter,

18:06.710 --> 18:11.924
and I'm sort of a shut-in,
but...we're safe.

18:15.427 --> 18:17.304
What do kids eat?

18:21.183 --> 18:24.394
How's the quesadilla?
- I had a brother.

18:28.106 --> 18:30.859
He died before he was born.

18:30.943 --> 18:33.153
Maybe he would have been
at home with a babysitter

18:33.237 --> 18:34.738
when Jeevan tried
to take me to my house.

18:34.822 --> 18:38.075
- I try not to think in maybes.

18:39.618 --> 18:41.286
- What happened to your leg?

18:43.288 --> 18:45.707
- Someone tried to blow me up.
- Why?

18:45.791 --> 18:48.919
- I was in the wrong place.

18:49.002 --> 18:50.212
Sri Lanka.

18:50.295 --> 18:53.257
There's a war there
that never ends.

18:53.340 --> 18:55.509
- What were you doing there?

18:55.592 --> 18:59.054
- Writing a story
for a magazine.

18:59.137 --> 19:00.973
- What magazine?

19:01.056 --> 19:03.517
- "Vanity Fair."

19:03.600 --> 19:05.185
You heard of it?

19:05.269 --> 19:06.562
- I don't know.

19:07.646 --> 19:11.066
- Well, I wasn't supposed
to be in the country.

19:11.149 --> 19:13.151
[sparse music]

19:13.235 --> 19:17.114
And I went to this bar,

19:17.197 --> 19:20.617
started chatting up the locals,

19:20.701 --> 19:22.995
you know, strangers, no agenda.

19:24.496 --> 19:28.584
Talked to this guy for a while.
Hired him as my guide.

19:28.667 --> 19:31.128
We walked.

19:31.211 --> 19:34.590
We walked about half a day.

19:34.673 --> 19:36.925
The last thing I remember
before...

19:37.009 --> 19:40.429
♪ ♪

19:40.512 --> 19:42.764
I look up at my guide
and he's running away.

19:42.848 --> 19:46.268
So I take a step,
and bang...

19:49.938 --> 19:51.565
Got blown up.

19:51.648 --> 19:54.318
I floated.

19:54.401 --> 19:56.361
[dramatic music]

19:56.445 --> 20:00.115
♪ ♪

20:00.198 --> 20:03.118
- Then what?
- Then I woke up in a hospital.

20:06.204 --> 20:07.789
No idea where I was,
what happened.

20:07.873 --> 20:08.832
I've got bandages everywhere,

20:08.916 --> 20:12.169
13 pieces of shrapnel
in my hip.

20:12.252 --> 20:14.421
I start screaming for help.

20:14.504 --> 20:18.050
And I look down
and Jeevan is there,

20:18.133 --> 20:21.511
asleep on the floor.

20:21.595 --> 20:25.307
So I'm thinking I'm either dead
or I'm home.

20:25.390 --> 20:29.436
- Where were you?
- Military base in Singapore.

20:29.519 --> 20:33.023
He got a 24-hour flight
on Siya's credit card.

20:33.106 --> 20:34.816
- [chuckles]

20:34.900 --> 20:36.234
I flew first class,
by the way.

20:39.947 --> 20:41.823
She never found out.

20:43.408 --> 20:43.659
- She did.

20:43.742 --> 20:46.495
- Really?

20:48.413 --> 20:51.625
[laughter]

20:57.255 --> 21:01.218
[tape rewinding,
playing intermittently]

21:05.764 --> 21:07.766
- Hey, Frank?

21:10.143 --> 21:11.228
You wanna be in my play?

21:13.730 --> 21:15.524
- Who else is in it?

21:15.607 --> 21:20.028
- So I think--

21:20.112 --> 21:21.029
sorry.

21:21.113 --> 21:25.367
I think we need to have a fire
in the spare room.

21:25.450 --> 21:26.243
- What?

21:28.036 --> 21:29.037
Hold on. Hey, Jeev.

21:29.121 --> 21:33.500
Can both of you meet me
at the table in ten minutes?

21:33.583 --> 21:34.668
I need to show you something.

21:34.751 --> 21:38.380
- Yeah.
- Okay.

21:47.889 --> 21:49.141
- I was working the other day,

21:49.224 --> 21:51.101
listening to the tapes
he sent me,

21:51.184 --> 21:52.853
and I heard something.

21:55.147 --> 21:59.234
It was the way he laughed.

21:59.317 --> 22:02.237
I--I couldn't
really believe it.

22:02.320 --> 22:05.449
And so I enhanced it
and I looped it.

22:05.532 --> 22:09.453
It's real.
It's a way to stay hot.

22:11.329 --> 22:14.291
[snippets of words
playing rhythmically]

22:21.339 --> 22:24.384
♪ Back in the days
when I was a teenager ♪

22:24.468 --> 22:27.095
♪ Before I had status
and before I had a pager ♪

22:27.179 --> 22:29.431
♪ You could find the Abstract
listenin' to hip-hop ♪

22:29.514 --> 22:31.475
♪ My pops used to say
it reminded him of bebop ♪

22:31.558 --> 22:32.642
- No.
- ♪ I said, "Well, Daddy ♪

22:32.726 --> 22:34.644
♪ "Don't you know
♪ that things go in cycles ♪

22:34.728 --> 22:36.772
♪ Way that Bobby Brown
is just ampin' like Michael?" ♪

22:36.855 --> 22:38.356
- Frank.
- ♪ It's all expected ♪

22:38.440 --> 22:39.816
♪ Things are for the lookin' ♪

22:39.900 --> 22:41.943
♪ If you got the money,
Quest is for the bookin' ♪

22:42.027 --> 22:43.278
[beat drops]
♪ Come on, everybody,

22:43.361 --> 22:44.571
♪ Let's get with the fly mode ♪

22:44.654 --> 22:47.282
♪ Still got room on
the truckload of black gold ♪

22:47.365 --> 22:49.659
♪ Listen to the rhyme
and get a mental picture ♪

22:49.743 --> 22:51.912
♪ Of this Black man
and Black woman venture ♪

22:51.995 --> 22:52.788
♪ Why do I say that ♪

22:52.871 --> 22:54.790
♪ 'Cause I gotta speak
the truth, man ♪

22:54.873 --> 22:56.958
♪ Doin' what we feel
for the music is the proof ♪

22:57.042 --> 22:59.628
♪ And planted on the ground,
the act is so together ♪

22:59.711 --> 23:02.089
♪ Bona fide strong,
you need leverage to sever ♪

23:02.172 --> 23:04.424
♪ The unit, yes, the unit,
yes, the unit called the jazz ♪

23:04.508 --> 23:05.759
♪ Is delivering each year ♪

23:05.842 --> 23:06.927
♪ An LP
filled with street goods ♪

23:07.010 --> 23:09.638
♪ You can find it on your rack
in your record store ♪

23:09.721 --> 23:11.181
♪ If you get the record,
then your thoughts ♪

23:11.264 --> 23:12.265
♪ Are adored and appreciated ♪

23:12.349 --> 23:14.976
both: ♪ 'Cause we're
ever so glad we made it ♪

23:15.060 --> 23:16.978
- ♪ We work hard,
so we gotta thank God ♪

23:17.062 --> 23:18.271
♪ Dishin' out the plastic ♪

23:18.355 --> 23:19.815
♪ Do the dance
till you're spastic ♪

23:19.898 --> 23:22.317
♪ If you diss, mm,
it gets drastic ♪

23:22.400 --> 23:24.861
♪ Listen to the rhyme 'cause
it's time to make gravy ♪

23:24.945 --> 23:25.987
♪ If it moves your booty ♪

23:26.071 --> 23:27.072
both: ♪ Then shake,
shake it, baby ♪

23:27.155 --> 23:29.658
- ♪ All the way to Africa,
AKA the motherland ♪

23:29.741 --> 23:32.160
♪ Stick out the left,
and I ask for the other hand ♪

23:32.244 --> 23:34.413
♪ That's the right hand,
brown man ♪

23:34.496 --> 23:37.415
♪ Only if you are noted
as my man ♪

23:37.499 --> 23:39.793
♪ If I get the credit,
then I'll think I deserve it ♪

23:39.876 --> 23:41.503
♪ If you fake moves, don't fix
your mouth to word it ♪

23:41.586 --> 23:45.382
♪ Get in the zone
of positivity, not negativity ♪

23:45.465 --> 23:47.300
♪ 'Cause we gotta strive
for longevity ♪

23:47.384 --> 23:49.511
♪ If you botch up,
what's in that ass ♪

23:49.594 --> 23:53.140
♪ What, a pair of Nikes ♪
both: ♪ Size 10 1/2 ♪

23:53.223 --> 23:54.850
- ♪ We gotta make moves ♪

23:54.933 --> 23:57.727
♪ Never, ever, ever
can we fake moves ♪

23:57.811 --> 23:59.938
♪ Yeah, we gotta make moves ♪

24:00.021 --> 24:03.150
♪ Never, ever, ever
can we fake moves ♪

24:03.233 --> 24:04.860
♪ We gotta make moves ♪

24:04.943 --> 24:08.071
♪ Never, ever, ever
can we fake moves ♪

24:08.155 --> 24:09.865
♪ We gotta make moves ♪

24:09.948 --> 24:12.659
♪ Never, ever, ever
can we fake the moves ♪

24:14.452 --> 24:18.373
[clock ticking]

24:18.456 --> 24:21.668
- I know.
I know you said 60, but--

24:23.837 --> 24:25.005
By the way, I don't think
the flu is out there anymore.

24:25.088 --> 24:29.217
- You have no data whatsoever.

24:29.301 --> 24:30.510
- What's the ration estimate
on the food, Frank?

24:34.806 --> 24:36.433
- 90 days.
- Oh, 90 days?

24:36.516 --> 24:38.810
So what is that,
12 days until we starve?

24:38.894 --> 24:41.521
There's your data.
We have to leave.

24:41.605 --> 24:44.065
First thing tomorrow.

24:44.149 --> 24:47.194
- Autobiography's not done.

24:47.277 --> 24:48.987
- Neither is my play,
but I'm almost done.

24:49.070 --> 24:51.198
- Something tells me neither
of you are gonna finish.

24:58.663 --> 25:02.042
Do you remember that--
that film

25:02.125 --> 25:04.211
with the soccer team
and they eat each other?

25:04.294 --> 25:06.296
You don't remember,
You're eight. Frank?

25:08.465 --> 25:09.424
- "Alive"?
- "Alive"? "Alive."

25:09.507 --> 25:12.219
- Yeah, it was a rugby team.
- Okay, great.

25:12.302 --> 25:13.470
They were proactive.
- You need more information.

25:13.553 --> 25:16.097
They had a plan.
They had somewhere to go.

25:16.181 --> 25:18.099
They had a map.
They knew what they--

25:18.183 --> 25:21.478
- Frank, this--this is
what we know.

25:23.104 --> 25:25.941
They survived.

25:26.024 --> 25:28.777
[dramatic string music]

25:28.860 --> 25:34.532
♪ ♪

25:36.493 --> 25:38.078
They survived.

25:41.039 --> 25:44.000
Yeah, they had to eat
each other, but they survived.

25:44.084 --> 25:46.503
- Hey.

25:46.586 --> 25:48.129
You okay?

25:48.213 --> 25:50.048
- Where have you been?

25:52.717 --> 25:56.304
- Watching.
- I spy with my little eye.

25:56.388 --> 25:57.847
- I thought he only started
speaking to himself

25:57.931 --> 26:01.017
at the cabin.

26:01.101 --> 26:03.144
- He started here.
- I don't get it.

26:03.228 --> 26:05.480
Yeah, I'm trying.

26:05.563 --> 26:09.067
Siya. I don't know, he won't.
This is Frank.

26:09.150 --> 26:11.027
- What's the cabin?
- He's not listening to me.

26:11.111 --> 26:13.363
- I don't know, Siya, but I'm
gonna convince him, okay?

26:13.446 --> 26:14.447
He'll come.

26:14.531 --> 26:16.491
I'll convince him, or...

26:16.574 --> 26:20.370
Kirsten will convince him
with her play.

26:22.831 --> 26:24.332
They've got a thing.

26:24.416 --> 26:27.168
I don't know.
They've got a thing.

26:29.087 --> 26:30.797
Siya.

26:30.880 --> 26:32.632
Yeah.

26:32.716 --> 26:35.844
Yes, I know.

26:35.927 --> 26:38.346
I just--okay, fine.

26:38.430 --> 26:40.348
I'll go across the hall
and I'll look west.

26:40.432 --> 26:45.437
Get him his data, his info,
his--

26:45.520 --> 26:46.938
okay, Siya, yes.

26:47.022 --> 26:48.148
I'm in the red. I gotta go.

26:50.150 --> 26:52.193
Frank.

26:52.277 --> 26:54.779
I'm opening the door.

26:56.531 --> 26:58.658
Frank, is that okay?

26:59.993 --> 27:02.370
Great.

27:02.454 --> 27:09.169
♪ ♪

27:14.591 --> 27:15.800
Hey.

27:17.510 --> 27:22.140
Look, I know it's hard
and it's scary, but...

27:23.850 --> 27:27.562
We're gonna starve to death
or freeze to death.

27:31.733 --> 27:35.070
And we can't wait for him
to get better.

27:35.153 --> 27:36.905
And we can't just write
plays and books.

27:36.988 --> 27:40.408
- I'm finished writing.

27:40.492 --> 27:42.660
- Oh.

27:42.744 --> 27:45.622
- We can do it tomorrow,
then go.

27:48.333 --> 27:50.085
But we have to perform it.

27:50.168 --> 27:52.754
- Okay, can we do it--
but can we do it, like, now?

27:52.837 --> 27:54.714
- The costumes
still aren't done.

27:55.298 --> 27:58.551
Tomorrow. I promise.

28:01.805 --> 28:03.264
What would you have done

28:03.348 --> 28:06.267
if you knew the flu was coming?

28:09.521 --> 28:13.400
- I would have come home
earlier from LA.

28:13.483 --> 28:17.695
And I would have spent time
with my mom

28:17.779 --> 28:18.613
before she died.

28:21.866 --> 28:23.868
And Siya.

28:25.453 --> 28:28.456
And that idiot, and we
would have been together.

28:30.667 --> 28:32.419
I would have just done--

28:35.547 --> 28:38.091
I would have made the choice
I wanted to make, you know?

28:44.264 --> 28:46.474
I'm always late for everything.

28:48.351 --> 28:50.603
How about you?

28:52.564 --> 28:53.648
- Said goodbye to Arthur.

28:56.693 --> 29:00.113
I didn't get to say
goodbye to anyone.

29:04.492 --> 29:08.246
- [sighs]
Yeah, well, say bye now.

29:08.329 --> 29:09.664
- He can't hear me.

29:09.747 --> 29:13.835
- Frank, I am opening the door.

29:16.880 --> 29:19.299
I mean, we don't even know
what Chicago's like out there.

29:19.382 --> 29:22.260
It might be fine.

29:22.343 --> 29:28.975
♪ ♪

29:39.944 --> 29:41.696
[coughs]

29:41.779 --> 29:47.785
♪ ♪

30:09.140 --> 30:10.683
- Hey, Luli!

30:13.645 --> 30:15.605
Luli!

30:15.688 --> 30:21.736
♪ ♪

30:33.790 --> 30:35.833
[wind whooshing]

30:42.215 --> 30:42.966
- Hello?

30:48.888 --> 30:51.015
[breathing heavily]

30:51.099 --> 30:58.898
♪ ♪

31:07.365 --> 31:09.909
[piano keys bang]

31:11.536 --> 31:13.162
[piano keys bang]

31:14.831 --> 31:17.792
[dramatic music]

31:17.875 --> 31:23.881
♪ ♪

31:30.430 --> 31:31.973
[plays piano key]

31:32.056 --> 31:38.813
♪ ♪

31:57.415 --> 32:00.501
[wind whistling]

32:02.629 --> 32:06.341
[light piano music]

32:06.424 --> 32:08.343
♪ ♪

32:08.426 --> 32:11.554
- Smells so bad.

32:11.638 --> 32:12.972
- Bodies.

32:15.058 --> 32:17.685
Oh, you get used to it.

32:17.769 --> 32:20.063
Hey, go talk to Frank, hey?

32:21.481 --> 32:23.691
Close the door.

32:30.782 --> 32:37.664
♪ ♪

32:37.747 --> 32:39.874
- What's that?

32:39.957 --> 32:42.377
- Well, I owe you a present,
don't I?

32:42.460 --> 32:47.215
[wind whooshing]

32:47.298 --> 32:50.968
I got this from our dadu,
our grandfather.

32:52.470 --> 32:55.098
Had it in my pocket that day
when I stepped on that mine.

32:56.432 --> 32:57.725
It's a compass.

33:00.937 --> 33:04.732
- We're going tomorrow.
Just come.

33:06.693 --> 33:08.736
- It's broken.

33:08.820 --> 33:10.905
[wind whistling]

33:14.617 --> 33:16.077
No matter how you stand,

33:16.160 --> 33:16.994
it tells you
you're looking east.

33:21.874 --> 33:24.669
Jeev just made me think of it.

33:24.752 --> 33:28.381
And that day, when you were
looking at the sunrise...

33:31.467 --> 33:33.428
That was a good feeling.

33:33.511 --> 33:36.472
[solemn music]

33:36.556 --> 33:43.604
♪ ♪

33:47.859 --> 33:49.986
- I made the whole play
the death scene.

33:52.196 --> 33:53.281
- Who am I?

33:53.364 --> 33:55.950
- Lonagan.

33:56.033 --> 33:59.120
- So it's...my death scene.

34:12.091 --> 34:14.469
- I found something,

34:14.552 --> 34:16.721
data boy.

34:18.890 --> 34:21.392
- Frank thinks
we should go east.

34:54.592 --> 34:55.927
[radio beeps]

35:02.058 --> 35:03.142
[radio beeps]

35:07.063 --> 35:08.397
[radio beeps]

35:12.276 --> 35:13.069
Call time is noon.

35:18.115 --> 35:21.244
- Okay, Kirsten,
this is really long,

35:21.327 --> 35:24.038
and there's not much light.

35:24.121 --> 35:28.042
So--
[static buzzing and warbling]

35:32.547 --> 35:34.465
Yes.

35:34.549 --> 35:36.968
Yes. This is now.
This is now.

35:38.386 --> 35:40.221
[distorted voice]

35:40.304 --> 35:44.016
Hello?
- I get scared. Where are you?

35:44.100 --> 35:46.435
- Minneapolis.

35:46.519 --> 35:48.688
- So nothing's
gotten rotten yet?

35:48.771 --> 35:51.357
The whole Mississippi
is bodies.

35:51.440 --> 35:52.608
I don't know
how they got in there,

35:52.692 --> 35:53.651
but it's plugged up.

35:53.734 --> 35:56.737
You could walk down it
and come to visit if--

35:56.821 --> 35:59.156
- Don't come here.
It's not safe.

36:04.287 --> 36:06.122
- It's just math.

36:38.696 --> 36:44.368
♪ ♪

36:44.452 --> 36:45.202
Let's do the play.

36:48.080 --> 36:50.124
I get tired of sifting
through the wreckage.

36:53.169 --> 36:55.838
- And I get tired
of watching you sift.

36:57.882 --> 37:00.468
What are you looking for?

37:00.551 --> 37:02.428
There's nothing out there.

37:08.684 --> 37:11.103
- Whatever didn't break.

37:12.730 --> 37:14.440
- Don't be nervous.

37:14.523 --> 37:16.233
- I'm not.

37:16.317 --> 37:19.695
You should go.
It's so gross.

37:19.779 --> 37:22.323
- It's fine.
- Why did you pull me on board?

37:22.406 --> 37:25.284
Why did you let me in here?

37:25.368 --> 37:26.786
- Protocol.

37:28.996 --> 37:31.165
- Where's the antidote?

37:31.248 --> 37:32.667
- Don't worry about it.

37:32.750 --> 37:35.169
- Or I was lonely.

37:38.464 --> 37:42.843
This strange and awful time...

37:42.927 --> 37:45.304
was the happiest of my life.

37:45.388 --> 37:48.349
[light music]

37:48.432 --> 37:55.189
♪ ♪

37:56.148 --> 37:58.859
You're the only friend
I've ever had.

38:04.073 --> 38:05.241
- You're going to die,
and I can't stop it.

38:07.702 --> 38:09.787
- That's true for everyone.

38:12.623 --> 38:12.832
- Good point.

38:12.915 --> 38:20.548
♪ ♪

38:21.799 --> 38:22.383
- Where did you
come from, Eleven?

38:25.469 --> 38:30.391
What were you doing,
floating out there by yourself?

38:30.474 --> 38:33.728
- I was trying to come home.

38:33.811 --> 38:37.773
You were the only person
who knew me from before.

38:37.857 --> 38:41.068
- Turn on the engines!

38:43.654 --> 38:45.614
- I can't do that.

38:45.698 --> 38:47.825
- Why not?

38:47.908 --> 38:51.620
I'm tired of that answer.

38:51.704 --> 38:53.080
- [groans]

38:53.164 --> 38:56.125
[dramatic music]

38:56.208 --> 38:59.253
♪ ♪

38:59.336 --> 39:00.337
- You should have listened.

39:04.050 --> 39:06.635
- You idiot!
You need him to survive!

39:06.719 --> 39:14.518
♪ ♪

39:16.771 --> 39:19.148
- Goodbye, Eleven.

39:24.195 --> 39:25.863
Say your line.

39:27.740 --> 39:30.951
Say it.

39:31.035 --> 39:37.708
♪ ♪

39:46.717 --> 39:48.677
Jeev.

39:48.761 --> 39:50.846
[cat meows]

39:50.930 --> 39:52.389
- Luli?

39:54.016 --> 39:57.812
[tense music]

39:57.895 --> 40:00.773
Jeevan! Frank!

40:04.318 --> 40:06.153
- Kirsten, run right now.

40:06.237 --> 40:07.613
Lock the door.
- Lock the door.

40:10.491 --> 40:13.953
[door slams]
- Hey, it's okay. It's okay.

40:14.036 --> 40:17.498
Whatever you need, man.
Okay. We're safe. It's safe.

40:21.085 --> 40:22.461
- Please leave.

40:22.545 --> 40:28.551
♪ ♪

40:33.931 --> 40:35.683
I live here now.

40:37.935 --> 40:40.563
- Okay.

40:40.646 --> 40:42.398
It's okay.
You can have the place.

40:42.481 --> 40:45.025
We're all packed.
We were just leaving.

40:45.109 --> 40:47.027
Right, Frank?

40:47.111 --> 40:53.993
♪ ♪

40:54.076 --> 40:55.870
Come on, Frank. Let's go.

41:01.417 --> 41:02.877
We're all packed up.
We were just leaving.

41:02.960 --> 41:04.086
It's fine.

41:07.923 --> 41:09.717
- I'm really sorry, man.

41:09.800 --> 41:11.469
- Don't.

41:13.971 --> 41:14.972
- I'm not leaving, man.

41:15.055 --> 41:16.390
- No, Frank.

41:16.473 --> 41:17.725
- It's my home.

41:17.808 --> 41:24.857
♪ ♪

41:26.108 --> 41:30.738
[both groaning and straining]

41:51.342 --> 41:54.929
"I remember damage,

41:55.012 --> 41:57.640
"then escape.

42:01.185 --> 42:03.020
"Then I found it again.

42:04.855 --> 42:07.358
My home."

42:10.694 --> 42:13.530
[grunting continues]

42:20.829 --> 42:23.666
- Frank!

42:23.749 --> 42:26.710
- Stay in your room.

42:26.794 --> 42:28.212
- Jeevan!

42:28.295 --> 42:32.883
- It's okay. He survives.

42:32.967 --> 42:35.427
You leave here with him.

42:36.720 --> 42:38.305
- Frank too?

42:39.265 --> 42:42.309
- You get to see him again.

42:46.397 --> 42:48.691
- I shouldn't have
done the play.

42:50.818 --> 42:53.195
- This didn't happen
because you did the play.

42:53.279 --> 42:56.991
This isn't your fault.

42:57.074 --> 42:59.576
This is just what happened.

43:01.787 --> 43:08.585
♪ ♪

43:33.110 --> 43:36.155
[blows landing]

43:44.079 --> 43:46.540
- [groans]

43:46.623 --> 43:49.960
Frank. Frank. Frank.

43:50.044 --> 43:52.379
- I'm okay. My armor.

43:52.463 --> 43:55.215
- Oh, God. I don't know.

43:55.299 --> 43:56.383
You can't just take it out
like that,

43:56.467 --> 43:57.843
I don't think, Frank.

43:59.136 --> 44:01.472
Siya. Siya.

44:01.555 --> 44:05.434
Siya! Siya! Come on!

44:05.517 --> 44:07.519
- Siya's dead, Jeev.

44:07.603 --> 44:11.732
- No, no, no.

44:11.815 --> 44:13.359
No, Frank.

44:16.028 --> 44:18.781
- I wanna lie down

44:18.864 --> 44:20.491
in my bed.

44:24.912 --> 44:28.582
- [sobbing]
Frank. Frank.

44:30.793 --> 44:36.799
♪ ♪

44:38.175 --> 44:43.347
[sobbing]
No.

44:43.430 --> 44:50.479
♪ ♪

45:33.397 --> 45:36.483
- Is that man gone?

45:38.402 --> 45:41.029
- We're safe, yeah.

45:47.619 --> 45:48.704
I thought your play was good.

46:02.134 --> 46:05.095
[somber music]

46:05.179 --> 46:12.978
♪ ♪

46:53.519 --> 46:56.230
Hey. Come here.

46:56.313 --> 47:03.320
♪ ♪

47:21.505 --> 47:23.840
- You were really good

47:23.924 --> 47:25.801
as Dr. Eleven.

47:32.015 --> 47:33.892
I almost made you Lonagan.

47:40.941 --> 47:45.445
- So what happens next...

47:45.529 --> 47:47.281
in your book?

47:47.364 --> 47:50.284
- It's the two of them,

47:50.367 --> 47:52.911
Dr. Eleven
and the Rebel Undersea Leader.

47:55.831 --> 47:57.332
For a while.

48:02.004 --> 48:04.089
Come.

48:04.172 --> 48:06.091
Just come.

48:11.805 --> 48:14.308
Open the door.

48:17.894 --> 48:19.146
- You have to go with Jeevan.

48:19.229 --> 48:26.987
♪ ♪

48:49.426 --> 48:52.346
[music building]

48:52.429 --> 48:59.478
♪ ♪

50:06.503 --> 50:09.506
I should probably go now.

50:50.672 --> 50:53.216
Goodbye, Frank.

50:53.300 --> 50:55.302
[poignant piano music]

50:55.385 --> 51:03.143
♪ ♪

52:24.641 --> 52:27.769
Wanted to say thank you

52:27.853 --> 52:31.731
for letting me stay here.
